               <person>
                  <persName role="owner" corresp="PRS0000">Täklä Haymanot is mentioned as the donor in the colophon and in the supplication formulas. His wife Wälättä Maryam (fol. 126va, and in the legend to the miniature on fol. 132r), his father Gäbrä Ḥäywät (fols. 27va, 38va, 126vb), and his mother Wälättä Kiros (fols. 55va, 71rb, 72ra, 126va) are also mentioned. His children are also mentioned in the colophon.&#xD;
Other names are written in the supplication formulas throughout the Ms., Wälättä Maryam (fols. 11ra, 12rb, 55va), Täsfa Mikaʾel (fols. 72vb, 87vb, 104vb), Gäbrä Ṣadǝqan (fols. 87vb, 104vb, 107rb).</persName>
